The paper presents a neural operator for Bayesian inference, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on particle flow methods, which are commonly used in machine learning for probabilistic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to sequential Bayesian inference, which falls under the category of control and dynamical systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper includes experiments on high-dimensional data, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
